WEBVTT

00:32.656 --> 00:35.325
♪ Mona Lisa

00:35.493 --> 00:39.413
♪ Mona Lisa
men have named you

00:39.581 --> 00:47.921
♪ You're so like the lady
with the mystic smile

00:48.089 --> 00:51.884
♪ Is it only
'cause you're lonely

00:52.052 --> 00:55.304
♪ They have blamed you

00:55.472 --> 00:59.475
♪ For that
Mona Lisa strangeness

00:59.642 --> 01:03.062
♪ In your smile?

01:03.229 --> 01:10.277
♪ Do you smile to tempt a lover,
Mona Lisa?

01:10.445 --> 01:18.827
♪ Or is this your way
to hide a broken heart?

01:18.995 --> 01:26.919
♪ Many dreams have been
brought to your doorstep

01:27.087 --> 01:31.465
♪ They just lie there

01:31.633 --> 01:35.594
♪ And they die there

01:35.762 --> 01:39.807
♪ Are you warm
Are you real

01:39.974 --> 01:43.811
♪ Mona Lisa?

01:43.978 --> 01:48.107
♪ Or just a cold and lonely

01:48.274 --> 01:53.862
♪ Lovely work of art? ♪

02:27.438 --> 02:29.398
(Knocks)

02:43.454 --> 02:45.372
(Knocks)

02:47.458 --> 02:49.418
Yeah?

02:51.296 --> 02:53.380
Do you want mum?

02:59.304 --> 03:02.723
- Mum!
- Who is it, love?

03:02.891 --> 03:06.518
- Jeannie, get inside. Get inside.
- Just let me talk to her.

03:06.603 --> 03:09.062
- You can't do this to me.
- You've been away too fucking long!

03:09.147 --> 03:12.441
- Mum, no!
- Just a minute! It's all I'm asking for!

03:12.525 --> 03:14.610
She don't know you, George,
and she don't wanna know you.

03:14.777 --> 03:16.195
She's my daughter!

03:16.362 --> 03:18.530
You can't do this to me!
I only came to see her!

03:18.698 --> 03:21.283
- No!
- You can't do this to me!

03:21.326 --> 03:23.952
- I'm sorry, love. I'm sorry.
- Get out!

03:24.037 --> 03:26.288
- Get out!
- Mum!

03:28.124 --> 03:30.083
You cow!

03:32.629 --> 03:34.588
I only came to say hello.

03:36.966 --> 03:39.927
- Hello!
- (Dog barks)

03:40.011 --> 03:42.638
(Onlookers laughing)

03:42.680 --> 03:44.723
Fuck off.

03:44.807 --> 03:46.892
Go on. Fuck off.

03:48.478 --> 03:50.395
Oi, you gonna clean all that up?

03:53.524 --> 03:56.443
Hey, hey! Take it easy, boys.
Okay? Hey!

03:56.527 --> 04:00.072
Just let him be, all right?
The man's upset. Okay?

04:00.156 --> 04:02.532
That's the right word,
George, eh? Upset?

04:07.830 --> 04:09.748
So where'd they all come from?

04:09.832 --> 04:11.959
- They live here.
- Since when?

04:12.043 --> 04:14.711
- Since you went inside.
- Jesus.

04:14.796 --> 04:17.255
- Did you get my last book?
- Yeah, yeah.

04:17.339 --> 04:19.423
Shouldn't have been
the driver, though.

04:19.509 --> 04:22.344
- Who should it have been, then?
- I could pin him in the first chapter.

04:22.387 --> 04:26.515
- Who should it have been, then?
- The Chinese fellow who fed the goldfish.

04:26.557 --> 04:30.060
- You didn't write it, George.
- No, no, I didn't, but if had, I'd...

04:31.646 --> 04:33.563
Christ!

04:33.648 --> 04:36.149
- You kept it.
- Aye, I kept it for you.

04:36.234 --> 04:38.443
- You keep it tuned?
- (Whistles)

04:46.619 --> 04:48.578
(Engine starts)

04:50.373 --> 04:53.041
♪ ('Mona Lisa')

04:58.089 --> 05:00.424
Why does she hate me, Thomas?

05:00.508 --> 05:04.136
- She doesn't.
- Yes, she does.

05:04.220 --> 05:06.888
You can never tell with women, George.
They're different.

05:06.973 --> 05:10.100
They wear skirts
and like to powder their noses,

05:10.184 --> 05:12.894
and when they go to heaven,
they get wings.

05:12.937 --> 05:15.897
- Like angels?
- Aye, like angels.

05:15.940 --> 05:18.900
- But angels are men, Thomas.
- Men?

05:18.943 --> 05:21.153
- Yeah.
- No one told me that.

05:21.237 --> 05:23.196
(Tyres screeching)

05:23.281 --> 05:26.908
It's true. Angels are men.

05:30.413 --> 05:33.415
(Dog barking)

05:33.499 --> 05:36.293
(Birds chirping)

05:40.548 --> 05:42.841
You got a big white rabbit
with long, floppy ears?

05:42.925 --> 05:45.594
No, but we have one
with short ears.

05:45.678 --> 05:48.638
- What's his name?
- His name is Arthur. He's over here.

05:48.723 --> 05:50.807
Oh, right.
He'll do. Yeah.

05:52.310 --> 05:55.312
- What is this, George?
- It's a rabbit.

05:57.482 --> 06:01.234
You're not gonna start
all that business again, are you?

06:01.319 --> 06:03.278
- Eh?
- Yeah.

06:03.321 --> 06:05.280
Why not?

06:05.323 --> 06:07.866
- Look, George, you can't go in there.
- Why not?

06:07.950 --> 06:10.118
It's different.

06:10.203 --> 06:12.162
What, Mortwell?
Is he different too?

06:12.246 --> 06:14.456
Very different.

06:14.540 --> 06:16.792
- Ah, we'll see.
- Come on, George. You're not going in there.

06:16.876 --> 06:20.629
(Scoffs)
I've done seven years for him, Thomas.

06:20.713 --> 06:23.382
Listen, George, you don't know
what they're up to now.

06:23.466 --> 06:26.885
- I don't give a fuck. Give us the rabbit.
- No, listen. What do you want it for?

06:26.969 --> 06:29.221
I'm gonna give it to him.

06:29.305 --> 06:31.306
It's up to you.

07:02.213 --> 07:04.172
We're closed.

07:05.800 --> 07:09.511
- Tell him, Terry.
- (Terry) Yeah, we're closed, sir.

07:12.557 --> 07:14.474
Hello, Terry.

07:16.811 --> 07:19.813
He'll have a lettuce,
and I'll have a Bloody Mary.

07:19.897 --> 07:23.358
- George.
- That's right. This is Arthur.

07:23.443 --> 07:26.736
- What are you doing here?
- Looking for Mortwell, Terry.

07:26.821 --> 07:29.990
Bit of work, you know.
What do you do now?

07:30.074 --> 07:33.577
- Whatever comes up.
- Yeah, but this is a knockin' shop.

07:33.661 --> 07:36.204
- Leave it out, George.
- So where is he?

07:36.289 --> 07:38.248
- Mortwell? He's not around.
- Yeah.

07:38.332 --> 07:42.335
- Well, he must be somewhere.
- Better ask Dudley, George.

07:42.420 --> 07:44.671
Through there?

07:44.755 --> 07:46.715
Cheers.

07:48.176 --> 07:50.802
(Computer beeping)

07:55.433 --> 07:57.392
Expecting me?

07:58.936 --> 08:00.896
- (Bleeping)
- Knew I was out?

08:00.938 --> 08:02.898
I suspected it, George.

08:02.940 --> 08:05.066
So where is he?

08:05.109 --> 08:07.068
Where's who?

08:07.111 --> 08:09.070
Mortwell.

08:09.113 --> 08:11.531
He's away, George.

08:11.616 --> 08:14.034
- South of France.
- He owes me, Dudley.

08:14.118 --> 08:16.495
- He said he'd look after me.
- He said a lot of things, George.

08:16.579 --> 08:19.039
Next time you see him,
give him that.

08:21.125 --> 08:23.752
Hey, George, George.

08:23.836 --> 08:25.795
Come on.

08:27.965 --> 08:30.759
- Look, we need a driver.
- I'm a driver.

08:30.801 --> 08:32.844
- Do you know what a bleeper is?
- A what?

08:33.346 --> 08:37.724
I can't understand it. How's that little
thing supposed to go bleep wherever I am?

08:37.892 --> 08:40.519
Well, it bounces off
the Post Office Tower, George.

08:40.602 --> 08:42.854
Miracle of modern technology.

08:42.938 --> 08:45.815
Yeah, but it hasn't got
an aerial or nothing.

08:45.900 --> 08:49.319
It doesn't need one.
I'll show you, right?

08:50.988 --> 08:53.323
- (Bleeping)
- What's that? Is that going?

08:53.407 --> 08:55.742
No, no. That's just a test,
to see if it's makin' a noise.

08:55.826 --> 08:57.744
Don't muck about with it,
for Christ's sake.

08:57.828 --> 08:59.996
You've been pulling that
bleedin' knob, ain't you?

09:00.081 --> 09:02.082
Bet you buggered it.

09:05.753 --> 09:07.671
What do you think?

09:07.755 --> 09:09.673
What do you do,
melt it down and eat it?

09:09.757 --> 09:12.801
No. They're ornamental, George.

09:12.885 --> 09:15.178
- Ornamental spaghetti?
- Aye.

09:15.263 --> 09:19.266
- I reckon it'll go a bomb.
- Where'd you get it?

09:19.350 --> 09:21.434
Contacts, George.

09:21.519 --> 09:24.229
Can't find plastic spaghetti
just anywhere.

09:24.313 --> 09:26.231
No.

09:26.315 --> 09:28.483
I don't suppose too many people
make it, do they?

09:28.568 --> 09:31.611
Well, the Japanese have
cornered the market.

09:31.696 --> 09:34.030
You fancy a fibreglass fruit flan?

09:35.533 --> 09:38.493
Or a polystyrene tutti-frutti?

09:38.536 --> 09:40.996
Fancy a cup of tea?

09:41.080 --> 09:43.039
What's it made of?

09:43.124 --> 09:45.125
Leaves.

09:46.669 --> 09:50.839
(Train passing)

10:27.752 --> 10:29.878
(Pager bleeping)

11:13.381 --> 11:16.383
(Women speaking French)

11:19.637 --> 11:21.638
♪ (Piano)

11:21.722 --> 11:24.641
(P.A.) Paging Mr. Carrington.

11:24.725 --> 11:27.018
Paging Mr. Carrington.

11:27.103 --> 11:29.104
Where's the bar?

11:29.188 --> 11:31.314
Take a seat, sir,
and I'll take your order.

11:33.401 --> 11:35.485
Paging Mr. Carrington.

11:56.507 --> 11:58.800
Thank you, sir.

12:03.848 --> 12:05.807
Doing business?

12:05.850 --> 12:09.144
- Darling, sorry I'm late.
- What's with the "darling"?

12:09.228 --> 12:11.146
For fuck's sake!

12:11.230 --> 12:14.149
What do you think this is,
the Honeymoon Hotel?

12:14.233 --> 12:17.819
Look, do you have business
in this hotel, or can I really help you?

12:21.031 --> 12:22.991
- Where's your car?
- Over there.

12:23.033 --> 12:25.994
- Pretend you know me, would you?
- I don't know you, do I?

12:26.036 --> 12:28.079
- Well, pretend you fucking well do!
- I beg your pardon.

12:34.253 --> 12:36.296
Not the back! The front!

12:37.715 --> 12:40.633
- So where did they get you from?
- Under a cabbage leaf.

12:48.601 --> 12:53.646
I have to work in these places. The bar boy
turns a blind eye, but the manager doesn't.

12:53.731 --> 12:56.107
- You gonna tell me where you want to go?
- The Lambert.

12:56.192 --> 12:58.109
- (Tyres screech)
- Jesus!

12:58.194 --> 12:59.903
- Sorry
- Didn't they tell you that?

12:59.987 --> 13:02.906
You're meant to be my date,
not my minicab driver.

13:02.990 --> 13:04.949
- (Horn honks)
- What does your date do?

13:05.034 --> 13:08.620
He looks after me, you dingbat.
He's meant to want to see me.

13:08.704 --> 13:10.747
- What if he don't?
- He pretends.

13:10.831 --> 13:13.041
How do you pretend?

13:13.125 --> 13:15.376
- Christ! Who sent you?
- Does it matter?

13:15.461 --> 13:19.005
- You're the tom, darling.
- Just shut up and drive, would you?

13:23.677 --> 13:26.471
Oh, can I have
a large Bloody Mary?

13:26.555 --> 13:28.640
I'm sitting here, all right?

13:34.897 --> 13:36.815
Hey, did you hear me?

13:36.899 --> 13:40.151
Are you serving here or just
wearing in a new pair of shoes?

13:40.236 --> 13:42.153
Oi!

13:51.455 --> 13:54.666
Do you want a drink?
They don't seem to serve you here.

13:54.750 --> 13:57.001
I've done it wrong again,
haven't I?

13:57.086 --> 14:00.338
Okay, I got it wrong.
That's - oof!

14:00.422 --> 14:04.384
What do you expect? I'm not used to
working in pissholes like this.

14:18.148 --> 14:24.904
♪ (Radio: orchestra)

14:46.343 --> 14:49.095
- That was quick.
- You were asleep.

14:49.179 --> 14:52.974
- Was I? How was he?
- I beg your pardon.

14:53.058 --> 14:56.311
- How was the Arab?
- None of your business.

14:56.395 --> 14:58.313
Oh. All right.

14:58.397 --> 15:00.440
Where to?

15:00.524 --> 15:02.609
King's Cross.

15:04.069 --> 15:06.529
(Women laughing)

15:08.824 --> 15:12.785
(Chattering)

15:15.331 --> 15:19.417
Hello.
Like a chocolate sandwich?

15:23.631 --> 15:25.548
(Woman laughing)

15:25.633 --> 15:28.259
- A bit downmarket, isn't it?
- Shut up.

15:32.181 --> 15:34.140
Drive on, please.

15:35.768 --> 15:37.727
(Woman) Here, don't go, mate!

15:50.366 --> 15:53.368
- And now?
- You leave me here.

15:55.329 --> 15:57.246
Good night, then.

15:57.331 --> 16:00.625
You have to get yourself
some clothes.

16:00.709 --> 16:03.252
Why would I have to get myself
some clothes?

16:03.337 --> 16:06.714
If you're to drive me.
Here. Use this.

16:06.757 --> 16:09.342
- I'm not having you paying me.
- Why not?

16:09.426 --> 16:13.221
- You don't even like me.
- I can claim it.

16:27.403 --> 16:29.320
Good night.

16:40.374 --> 16:43.209
- Is this real?
- Aye, of course.

16:43.293 --> 16:46.838
- A present for you.
- All right.

16:46.922 --> 16:50.383
- Is it good? Yeah?
- It's brilliant. Aye.

16:52.094 --> 16:54.804
- Somebody's murdering opera singers, right?
- Right.

16:54.888 --> 16:59.392
And after every murder,
they'll leave a Percheron.

16:59.476 --> 17:01.728
- What's a Percheron?
- A kind of horse.

17:01.812 --> 17:06.148
You mean like a white horse
that pulls a milk cart?

17:06.233 --> 17:08.526
- Aye, that kind of thing.
- All right.

17:08.609 --> 17:11.738
- And?
- Well, then it gets complicated.

17:11.821 --> 17:14.198
- It might just spoil it for you.
- Oh.

17:21.415 --> 17:23.790
(Laughing, chattering)

18:05.709 --> 18:07.627
Christ.

18:07.711 --> 18:09.670
What do you think?

18:09.755 --> 18:11.714
Jesus.

18:14.009 --> 18:16.886
- You don't like 'em?
- Do you?

18:18.680 --> 18:21.933
- Well, I bought 'em, didn't I?
- You bought them, all right.

18:22.017 --> 18:25.186
Ah, fuck. Here.
Here's your change.

18:25.229 --> 18:28.272
Not here.
For Jesus' sake!

18:45.582 --> 18:48.501
You're as much cover
as a pair of fishnet tights.

18:48.585 --> 18:50.962
I may as well be wearing
a sign around my neck.

18:51.046 --> 18:53.214
All you're missing
is the gold medallion.

18:53.257 --> 18:57.051
- You don't like them either?
- Fucking hate them.

18:57.136 --> 18:59.178
Right.

18:59.263 --> 19:02.723
See, I'm cheap. I can't help it.
God made me that way.

19:02.808 --> 19:04.725
Being cheap is one thing.

19:04.810 --> 19:07.562
Looking cheap is another.
That really takes talent.

19:07.604 --> 19:09.814
Some women are whores.
Some whores are black.

19:09.898 --> 19:11.858
You take what you're given,
don't ya?

19:11.942 --> 19:15.862
I didn't ask to drive you around.
I was given you, same as you was given me.

19:15.946 --> 19:20.116
- The only difference is, you complain and I don't.
- ♪ (Radio: 'Mona Lisa')

19:20.200 --> 19:22.577
- Turn it off! You heard me. Turn it off.
- No.

19:22.619 --> 19:25.746
You asked me to buy clothes.
I bought 'em!

19:25.789 --> 19:28.249
But you make remarks.
Anybody ever teach you manners?

19:28.333 --> 19:30.251
- You want to work for me?
- No!

19:31.712 --> 19:33.963
- (Tyres screeching)
- (Horns honking)

19:39.928 --> 19:43.139
Get out. Get fucking out!

19:44.808 --> 19:47.185
Now tell me I'm fired.

19:47.269 --> 19:49.270
- All right. You're fired.
- Lovely.

19:49.354 --> 19:51.355
I'm fired, and you're streetwalking.

19:51.440 --> 19:54.192
- (Horn honking)
- Fuck off!

19:56.028 --> 19:57.862
You swine.

19:57.946 --> 20:01.282
(Horn honking)

20:01.325 --> 20:04.994
(Different horns honking)

20:07.372 --> 20:09.707
Go screw yourself!

20:09.791 --> 20:12.460
- (Men yelling)
- (Horns honking)

20:30.979 --> 20:32.813
- Piss off.
- Look, come on!

20:35.692 --> 20:39.654
Look, come on. You can't stand
in the middle of the road.

20:39.738 --> 20:41.781
You're gonna get run over.

20:41.865 --> 20:45.993
Come on, please.
Please. I'm sorry.

20:46.036 --> 20:50.331
All right, I've wasted your money.
I look ridiculous. I'm sorry.

20:50.374 --> 20:53.668
- You don't look that bad.
- Well, bad enough.

20:53.752 --> 20:56.462
Get in the car, eh?
Madame?

20:58.674 --> 21:02.134
- We're late.
- All right, all right. I'm... I'm sorry.

21:03.428 --> 21:06.973
- (Horn honking)
- We're gonna get run over here.

21:14.856 --> 21:17.817
- Where'd you wanna go?
- Up to Highgate.

21:28.036 --> 21:31.914
♪ (Car stereo)

21:45.304 --> 21:48.055
Madam thought you might like
some refreshments, sir.

21:48.098 --> 21:50.558
Oh, thank you very much.
Will she be long?

21:50.600 --> 21:54.228
- No more than usual, sir.
- Right. Cheers.

22:01.361 --> 22:04.405
♪ (Humming 'Mona Lisa')

22:15.542 --> 22:18.002
(Man)
See you next Friday.

22:22.257 --> 22:24.925
- Uh, who do I give this to?
- To me.

22:24.968 --> 22:28.763
Oh, thank you.
Thanks a lot. Ta. See ya.

22:30.640 --> 22:35.353
He took his time.
What, he fall asleep halfway through?

22:35.437 --> 22:37.897
Well, you never know
with these darkies, do ya?

22:37.981 --> 22:40.483
Oh. I'm sorry.

22:40.567 --> 22:43.361
- I told you I was cheap, didn't I?
- Very.

22:43.445 --> 22:45.488
Much obliged.

22:45.572 --> 22:47.490
- Where to now?
- King's Cross.

22:47.574 --> 22:52.078
Back to the meat rack.
Your wish is my command.

23:14.768 --> 23:16.977
(George)
Jesus. They're so young.

23:18.188 --> 23:20.606
Here, tell me something.

23:20.690 --> 23:23.234
What?

23:23.318 --> 23:25.986
Do they ever want you back?

23:26.071 --> 23:29.198
- Who?
- Your clients.

23:29.282 --> 23:34.161
- Always.
- What, they fall in love with you?

23:36.706 --> 23:38.707
Well, do they?

23:40.460 --> 23:44.797
Sometimes they fall for
what they think I am.

23:44.881 --> 23:47.383
What do they think you are?

23:47.467 --> 23:50.594
What you think. A black whore.

23:50.679 --> 23:54.640
- Did I say that?
- What do you think, then?

23:56.393 --> 23:58.352
Well, you ain't no night nurse.

23:58.395 --> 24:00.688
I ain't no night nurse.

24:02.691 --> 24:06.360
Let's say you're a...
a lady.

24:06.445 --> 24:08.362
Why, thank you.

24:08.447 --> 24:10.364
Yeah.

24:22.586 --> 24:25.546
So what about this job, then?

24:25.589 --> 24:27.715
Well, it's...

24:27.799 --> 24:30.050
- It's just driving, you know.
- Yeah?

24:30.093 --> 24:32.052
Driving who?

24:33.722 --> 24:35.848
A tall, thin, black tart.

24:35.932 --> 24:39.268
- I could write a book about it.
- Too many T's.

24:39.352 --> 24:41.770
No, no.
He comes out of nick,

24:41.855 --> 24:43.772
and they owe him one,

24:43.857 --> 24:47.860
and they give him a job
driving a tall, thin, black tart,

24:47.944 --> 24:49.862
and she fuckin' hates him.

24:49.946 --> 24:53.032
- Treats him like a doormat.
- And he hates her?

24:54.868 --> 24:57.745
- Well, kind of.
- You mean he likes her?

24:57.787 --> 25:00.247
- He don't even know her, does he?
- (Pager bleeping)

25:00.332 --> 25:02.291
She's early.

25:11.468 --> 25:14.386
- You look better in the daytime.
- Oh, so do you.

25:14.471 --> 25:16.597
- Where do you want to go?
- Down here.

25:16.681 --> 25:19.767
- What, you wanna walk?
- Yes. It's good for you.

25:19.809 --> 25:23.687
- A bit early, isn't it?
- I know, but the early bird catches the worm.

25:23.772 --> 25:25.689
Clever little bastard.

25:30.654 --> 25:32.988
- In here?
- Yes.

25:35.659 --> 25:38.285
- You got business here?
- Yeah.

25:38.328 --> 25:40.287
Hold this.

25:40.372 --> 25:42.498
