♪ Poor old Michael Finnegan
begin again

01:23:36.136 --> 01:23:38.762
♪ There was an old man
called Michael Finnegan

01:23:38.847 --> 01:23:41.306
- ♪ He grew whiskers on... ♪
- Don't you know any other songs?

01:23:44.853 --> 01:23:47.354
♪ Was an old man
called Michael Finnegan

01:23:47.439 --> 01:23:50.107
(Both)
♪ He grew whiskers on his chin-egan ♪

01:24:11.546 --> 01:24:13.547
Want a cup of tea?

01:24:15.675 --> 01:24:18.260
Come on. Come on.

01:24:39.741 --> 01:24:42.076
You like ice cream?

01:24:42.160 --> 01:24:44.495
It's the only thing I can eat.

01:24:44.537 --> 01:24:46.622
- What do you mean?
- You know.

01:24:48.124 --> 01:24:50.042
No, I don't know.

01:24:50.126 --> 01:24:53.212
I can't take food
anymore. Real food.

01:24:54.923 --> 01:24:57.508
Well, what can you take?

01:24:57.550 --> 01:25:00.344
You don't know anything, do you?

01:25:00.428 --> 01:25:03.305
Nah. No, I don't know anything.

01:25:03.389 --> 01:25:06.350
I don't mean to be rude.
I like you.

01:25:06.392 --> 01:25:08.477
Oh. I'm glad.

01:25:09.979 --> 01:25:12.356
- Do you like me?
- I don't know you, do I?

01:25:14.192 --> 01:25:16.110
She likes me.

01:25:19.948 --> 01:25:21.949
She really likes me.

01:25:39.175 --> 01:25:41.802
I'll, uh... I'll wait out here, all right?

01:25:41.886 --> 01:25:43.804
Thanks, George.

01:25:56.109 --> 01:25:58.944
- You like her, don't you?
- Yeah.

01:26:04.659 --> 01:26:07.327
- Do you?
- I don't know her, do I?

01:26:09.497 --> 01:26:13.250
Let's face it. You're not a very good bet,
though, are you, George?

01:26:13.334 --> 01:26:15.586
Uh-uh.

01:26:15.670 --> 01:26:19.298
- (Thomas) So what was the story, then?
- Complicated.

01:26:19.382 --> 01:26:22.926
More complicated than
the story about the horse?

01:26:23.011 --> 01:26:25.721
Much more.

01:26:25.805 --> 01:26:28.724
I better be gettin' back, then.
What do you think?

01:26:30.101 --> 01:26:33.478
- Yeah, yeah.
- You gonna be all right, then, eh?

01:26:33.563 --> 01:26:35.564
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

01:26:51.706 --> 01:26:53.874
(Neighing)

01:26:56.711 --> 01:26:58.754
(Neighing)

01:27:21.236 --> 01:27:23.153
(Horn honking,
tyres screeching)

01:27:37.585 --> 01:27:39.670
- Where is she?
- (Simone) Here.

01:27:41.923 --> 01:27:44.216
- Who is he, then?
- He's a friend of mine.

01:27:44.300 --> 01:27:47.094
He's the ice cream man,
Mr. Whippy.

01:27:47.178 --> 01:27:49.721
- Left your van outside, have you?
- Shh, shh.

01:27:49.806 --> 01:27:53.433
(Moaning, crying)

01:27:55.436 --> 01:27:57.854
What's the matter
with her?

01:27:57.897 --> 01:28:00.857
Do me a favour, would you?
Get this from the chemist.

01:28:04.237 --> 01:28:08.365
Oh, uh, here, listen.
You better have this.

01:28:08.449 --> 01:28:10.367
Here you are.

01:28:11.452 --> 01:28:13.453
You never know, do you?

01:29:26.319 --> 01:29:28.445
- Thanks.
- You brought the ice cream.

01:30:06.025 --> 01:30:08.068
(Man)
What time is it?

01:30:09.987 --> 01:30:12.030
(Woman)
Ten minutes till twelve.

01:30:22.834 --> 01:30:26.420
(Doorbell chiming
'The Wedding March')

01:30:26.504 --> 01:30:29.423
(Door opening on television)

01:30:31.676 --> 01:30:33.593
(Older Man)
Hello, hello.

01:30:36.097 --> 01:30:38.557
- (Young Man)
Do you do the marrying?
- That's my business.

01:30:38.599 --> 01:30:40.600
- I have a $30 wedding...
- She asleep?

01:30:40.685 --> 01:30:42.602
Yes.

01:30:44.105 --> 01:30:46.106
Like babes in the wood.

01:30:46.190 --> 01:30:50.402
(Conversation continues
on television)

01:30:50.486 --> 01:30:52.487
I like the seaside.

01:30:54.073 --> 01:30:56.032
I've always
liked the seaside.

01:30:57.577 --> 01:31:01.163
- Do you like the seaside?
- Come for a walk on the pier.

01:31:02.874 --> 01:31:04.791
(Young Man)
I'll buy one.

01:31:04.876 --> 01:31:07.043
(Older Man)
Um, this one will do it.

01:31:12.925 --> 01:31:14.968
First you gotta
sign your names.

01:31:15.052 --> 01:31:18.013
(Gulls screeching)

01:31:24.479 --> 01:31:27.272
Did you used to do
this walk?

01:31:27.356 --> 01:31:29.357
Every day.

01:31:30.443 --> 01:31:33.403
- With your gentlemen?
- Sometimes.

01:31:33.488 --> 01:31:35.864
- ♪ (Calliope playing)
- Come here.

01:31:35.948 --> 01:31:39.576
Come on. Show me
the sights, eh?

01:31:39.619 --> 01:31:43.246
Now then, did you dance with him?
Did you waltz, eh?

01:31:43.289 --> 01:31:45.290
Did you tango?

01:31:47.418 --> 01:31:49.628
Come on.
I'll buy you a present, eh?

01:31:50.796 --> 01:31:52.714
Let's have a party,
shall we?

01:31:52.798 --> 01:31:54.716
Here you are, mate.
(Laughing)

01:31:58.763 --> 01:32:01.723
Don't run away.

01:32:01.807 --> 01:32:05.185
What you think?
Eh? Here.

01:32:08.648 --> 01:32:11.566
Beautiful. Cover those
fuckin' eyes, eh?

01:32:11.651 --> 01:32:13.568
Told you I was cheap,
didn't I?

01:32:13.653 --> 01:32:17.197
Seven years away,
I can do with a tan.

01:32:17.281 --> 01:32:19.407
- Don't run away from me.
- Leave me!

01:32:19.492 --> 01:32:21.785
You got a tan.
Where'd you get your tan?

01:32:21.827 --> 01:32:24.412
Can't I have a tan?
What's wrong with me?

01:32:24.497 --> 01:32:27.249
(George) What's the matter?
Am I too old for you?

01:32:27.333 --> 01:32:30.126
Am I too cheap?
Eh? You know.

01:32:30.211 --> 01:32:32.420
Come on.
Just show me the sights.

01:32:32.505 --> 01:32:35.173
You know, get me some Brighton Rock.
That's all I want.

01:32:35.258 --> 01:32:37.175
We're on holiday,
aren't we?

01:32:37.260 --> 01:32:39.970
We're going to have fun, like men
and women do. They have fun.

01:32:40.012 --> 01:32:42.514
They walk arm in arm,
you know?

01:32:42.598 --> 01:32:45.183
- You know? And they all kiss.
- No.

01:32:48.521 --> 01:32:50.855
Because they love each other,

01:32:50.940 --> 01:32:54.150
and they get married
so they can love each other more...

01:32:54.235 --> 01:32:56.403
and have a little baby.

01:32:56.487 --> 01:32:58.446
Only a little one.

01:32:58.531 --> 01:33:01.449
And he fights with
his fuckin' mother-in-law.

01:33:01.534 --> 01:33:03.451
You know the way it is...

01:33:03.536 --> 01:33:06.538
between men and fuckin' women!

01:33:06.622 --> 01:33:08.623
- Eh?
- (Whimpering)

01:33:08.708 --> 01:33:10.834
Come on. Say something.
Anything. Say it.

01:33:10.918 --> 01:33:14.838
(Whimpering)
I'm sorry. I can't.

01:33:14.922 --> 01:33:17.757
- You're worried?
- Yes.

01:33:17.842 --> 01:33:19.926
So are you gonna tell me?

01:33:21.846 --> 01:33:24.139
Tell you what?

01:33:24.223 --> 01:33:26.891
As my friend Thomas would say,
the whole story.

01:33:45.578 --> 01:33:48.163
You like her, don't you?

01:33:48.247 --> 01:33:50.248
Of course I like her.

01:33:51.417 --> 01:33:53.877
Yeah, but you like her in that...

01:33:53.961 --> 01:33:56.379
special way.

01:33:56.464 --> 01:33:59.341
In the songs.

01:33:59.425 --> 01:34:01.885
What songs?

01:34:01.927 --> 01:34:04.262
Well, I've sold myself
for a couple of dykes.

01:34:05.931 --> 01:34:07.891
She needs me, George.

01:34:09.101 --> 01:34:11.728
And you needed me
to get her.

01:34:11.812 --> 01:34:13.813
Did you ever need someone?

01:34:16.442 --> 01:34:18.568
All the time.

01:34:31.290 --> 01:34:33.583
George!

01:34:33.668 --> 01:34:35.669
George!

01:35:17.169 --> 01:35:19.629
Hey, come on!

01:35:26.929 --> 01:35:29.139
Where the fuck is he?

01:36:05.509 --> 01:36:07.594
(Mortwell)
Shh.

01:36:11.640 --> 01:36:13.641
You bloody fool, George.

01:36:14.894 --> 01:36:17.520
- You bloody fool.
- Can't you leave it, Denny?

01:36:17.605 --> 01:36:21.149
No, George, I can't leave it at all.

01:36:23.611 --> 01:36:25.612
Can I, lovey?

01:36:28.866 --> 01:36:30.825
Look at this tart.

01:36:33.287 --> 01:36:35.497
What you do it for, George?

01:36:35.581 --> 01:36:38.249
- I mean, look at her. It's all right.
- (Gasps)

01:36:38.334 --> 01:36:42.045
I'm not gonna hurt you.
Your pimp will do that for me. See?

01:36:43.339 --> 01:36:45.423
I'm givin' 'em both back to you.

01:36:47.218 --> 01:36:50.053
- The two of 'em.
- (Simone shrieks)

01:36:50.095 --> 01:36:51.971
Don't touch me! Don't!

01:36:52.056 --> 01:36:54.307
- She's got a gun, George! Ahh!
- (Gunshot)

01:36:54.391 --> 01:36:57.644
- (Screaming)
- She blew me fuckin' toes off, George!

01:36:57.728 --> 01:36:59.687
- (Simone) It hurts now, doesn't it?
- George!

01:36:59.772 --> 01:37:02.023
- (Gunshot)
- It really fuckin' hurts!

01:37:02.107 --> 01:37:03.900
- (Gunshot)
- (Cathy screaming)

01:37:03.943 --> 01:37:05.735
- Simone!
- (Cathy crying)

01:37:09.949 --> 01:37:11.950
Hey!

01:37:18.415 --> 01:37:22.335
- Come on. Come on.
- What, hurt you too?

01:37:22.419 --> 01:37:27.090
You fuckin' cow!
You fuckin' cow!

01:37:27.174 --> 01:37:29.425
You would've done it,
wouldn't you?

01:37:29.468 --> 01:37:31.553
You would've done it!

01:37:31.637 --> 01:37:33.763
I'm just another
fuckin' punter to you!

01:37:33.806 --> 01:37:36.891
(Sobbing)

01:37:41.981 --> 01:37:44.107
You fuckin' cow.

01:37:49.488 --> 01:37:51.489
You fuckin'...

01:37:59.081 --> 01:38:01.207
(Sobbing)

01:38:24.356 --> 01:38:27.358
(Sobbing)

01:39:22.247 --> 01:39:24.999
(George)
She was trapped.

01:39:25.084 --> 01:39:28.670
From the first time
he met her, she was trapped.

01:39:28.754 --> 01:39:31.255
Like a bird in a cage.

01:39:31.340 --> 01:39:33.341
But he couldn't see it.

01:39:33.425 --> 01:39:36.010
Well, he liked her too much.

01:39:36.095 --> 01:39:39.097
And he was the sort who couldn't see
what was in front of his face,

01:39:39.139 --> 01:39:41.391
and there she was, in pain.

01:39:41.475 --> 01:39:44.227
When you're soppy
about someone, well,

01:39:44.311 --> 01:39:46.729
you can't see things
like that, can you?

01:39:46.814 --> 01:39:49.774
And there he was,
soppy sod.

01:39:49.858 --> 01:39:51.901
Oh, she had faith in him.

01:39:51.986 --> 01:39:55.238
She believed in him, and he
had a lot of hope for her.

01:39:57.449 --> 01:39:59.492
But then there was love.

01:40:00.703 --> 01:40:04.247
Yeah. Yeah, she was
in love, all right.

01:40:04.289 --> 01:40:06.582
- Uh-huh.
- She really was.

01:40:08.252 --> 01:40:12.046
But not with him.
(Chuckles)

01:40:12.131 --> 01:40:14.966
- And that's the story.
- That's the whole story?

01:40:16.093 --> 01:40:18.761
Well, almost.

01:40:18.846 --> 01:40:21.931
- Hello, Dad.
- Comin'. Hello.

01:40:24.852 --> 01:40:28.354
How are you?
You're lookin' well.

01:40:29.648 --> 01:40:31.649
Excuse me.

01:40:41.326 --> 01:40:44.120
♪ Mona Lisa

01:40:44.204 --> 01:40:47.540
♪ Mona Lisa
men have named you

01:40:48.959 --> 01:40:55.465
♪ You're so like the lady
with the mystic smile

01:40:56.925 --> 01:41:00.762
